## 3. Where to Host

### Platform Comparison

| Platform | Free Tier | PostgreSQL | Ease | Best For |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **[Railway.app](https://railway.app)** | $5 free credit/mo | ✅ One-click | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Easiest for beginners |
| **[Render](https://render.com)** | Free (sleeps after 15min) | ✅ Free 90 days | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Free tier |
| **[Neon](https://neon.tech)** + Render | Free Postgres forever | ✅ Generous free | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Best free Postgres |
| **DigitalOcean Droplet** | $4/mo | Manual setup | ⭐⭐⭐ | Full control, persistent disk |
| **AWS EC2** | 1 year free tier | RDS free tier | ⭐⭐ | Enterprise scale |
| **Heroku** | $5/mo (Eco) | ✅ Add-on | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Classic PaaS |

> [!TIP]
> **My recommendation: Railway.app** — It's the simplest. You connect your GitHub repo, set environment variables, and it auto-deploys. PostgreSQL is one click away. The $5/month free credit is enough for a college project.

