## 4. Step-by-Step: Deploy on Railway

### Prerequisites
- A [GitHub](https://github.com) account (free)
- Your project pushed to a GitHub repository

### Step 1: Push Code to GitHub

```bash
# In your project folder (d:\ML\deepface\face_recognition)
git init                          # Already done
git add .
git commit -m "Production ready"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/attendance-system.git
git push -u origin main
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **NEVER push [.env](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/.env) to GitHub!** Your [.gitignore](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/.gitignore) already excludes it. Double-check before pushing. Your [.env](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/.env) contains your email password.

### Step 2: Create Railway Account
1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app)
2. Sign up with your GitHub account
3. You get **$5 free credit per month** (no credit card needed initially)

### Step 3: Create a New Project
1. Click **"New Project"**
2. Select **"Deploy from GitHub Repo"**
3. Connect your GitHub and select your `attendance-system` repository
4. Railway will auto-detect your [Dockerfile](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/Dockerfile) and start building

### Step 4: Add PostgreSQL Database
1. In your Railway project dashboard, click **"+ New"** → **"Database"** → **"PostgreSQL"**
2. Railway creates a PostgreSQL instance and gives you a connection URL
3. Click on the PostgreSQL service → **"Variables"** tab
4. Copy the `DATABASE_URL` value (it looks like `postgresql://user:pass@host:port/dbname`)

### Step 5: Set Environment Variables
1. Click on your **app service** (not the database)
2. Go to the **"Variables"** tab
3. Add these variables:

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | `postgresql://...` (from Step 4 — Railway can auto-link this) |
| `SECRET_KEY` | Any random string, e.g. `my-super-secret-key-2026` |
| `SENDER_EMAIL` | `anshraythatha123@gmail.com` |
| `SENDER_PASSWORD` | Your Gmail app password |
| `PORT` | `8080` (Railway sets this automatically) |

### Step 6: Deploy
Railway will automatically rebuild and deploy. Check the **"Deployments"** tab for logs.

### Step 7: Access Your App
Railway gives you a URL like `https://attendance-system-production.up.railway.app`. Share this with your faculty!

---

## 5. Step-by-Step: Deploy on Render

### Step 1: Push to GitHub (same as above)

### Step 2: Create Render Account
1. Go to [render.com](https://render.com) and sign up with GitHub

### Step 3: Create a PostgreSQL Database
1. Dashboard → **"New"** → **"PostgreSQL"**
2. Name: `attendance-db`
3. Plan: **Free** (90-day limit) or **Starter** ($7/mo)
4. Click **Create**
5. Copy the **Internal Database URL**

### Step 4: Create a Web Service
1. **"New"** → **"Web Service"**
2. Connect your GitHub repo
3. Settings:
   - **Environment**: Docker
   - **Plan**: Free (or Starter $7/mo for always-on)
4. Add environment variables (same as Railway Step 5)
5. Click **Deploy**

> [!NOTE]
> Render's free tier **sleeps after 15 minutes of inactivity** and takes ~30 seconds to wake up. For a college system used during class hours, the **Starter plan ($7/mo)** is recommended to keep it always on.

