## 7. Environment Variables & Secrets

**Never hardcode secrets.** Update your [app.py](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/app.py) to read from environment:

```python
# app.py — already partially done
app.secret_key = os.environ.get('SECRET_KEY', os.urandom(24))
```

Your [.env](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/.env) file (for local development only):
```
SECRET_KEY=my-local-dev-key
DATABASE_URL=          # Leave empty to use SQLite locally
SENDER_EMAIL=anshraythatha123@gmail.com
SENDER_PASSWORD=bjrxmajojbeohqse
```

On the cloud platform, set these same variables in the dashboard (never commit [.env](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/.env) to Git).

---

## 8. Custom Domain (Optional)

If your college has a domain like `gec.ac.in`, you can set up a subdomain:

1. **Railway/Render**: Go to Settings → Custom Domain
2. Add `attendance.gec.ac.in` (or whatever you want)
3. Add a **CNAME record** in your college's DNS panel pointing to the platform's URL
4. Railway/Render will auto-provision an SSL certificate (HTTPS)

---

## 9. Troubleshooting

| Problem | Solution |
|---|---|
| **Build fails** | Check that [requirements.txt](file:///d:/ML/deepface/face_recognition/requirements.txt) has all dependencies. Look at build logs. |
| **App crashes on start** | Usually missing environment variables. Check `SECRET_KEY` and `DATABASE_URL` are set. |
| **Face recognition slow** | InsightFace model loads on first request (~10-20s). This is normal. Increase gunicorn `--timeout` to 120+. |
| **DB data lost after redeploy** | You're using SQLite on an ephemeral filesystem. Switch to PostgreSQL. |
| **"Address already in use"** | The `PORT` env var isn't set. Railway/Render set it automatically. |
| **Large image files** | Consider storing `registered_faces/` in cloud storage (AWS S3 / Cloudinary) for production. |
| **Gmail SMTP blocked** | Use an [App Password](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords), not your real password. |

